word_group.brief_definition: 省政府；省级政府；省委省政府

bilingual.source: We plan to visit the provincial capital of this province.
bilingual.target: 我们计划去参观这个省的省会。

bilingual.source: The provincial capital of each province is usually its largest city.
bilingual.target: 每个省的省会通常是该省最大的城市。

bilingual.source: Want to be a provincial police chief?
bilingual.target: 想成为一个省的警察首长吗？

bilingual.source: Provincial superior courts may administer federal law.
bilingual.target: 省的高级法院则可以适用联邦的法律。

bilingual.source: The provincial capital and largest city of Prince Edward Island.
bilingual.target: 爱德华太子岛省的省会和最大城市。

bilingual.source: The project has also been listed as the National and provincial Torch Plan Project.
bilingual.target: 此开发项目还被列为国家和省的火炬计划项目。

bilingual.source: Thus, China's provincial GDP tabulations add up to far more than the countrywide estimate.
bilingual.target: 因此，中国各省的国内生产总值表格加起来远远超过全国的估计。

bilingual.source: He therefore ensured that provincial governors actually governed the provinces instead of exploiting them.
bilingual.target: 因此他确保行省的统治者是管理行省而不是剥削行省。

bilingual.source: The car company of the same name had gained provincial level approval to develop an investment area of its own.
bilingual.target: 相同的名字汽车公司已经得到省的水平赞成发展一个它自己的投资区域。

bilingual.source: Munich, southern Germany is the preferred tourist spots, is the provincial capital of Bavaria, has its own unique cultural characteristics.
bilingual.target: 慕尼黑是德国南面的旅游点首选，亦是巴伐利亚省的首府，拥有独特的文化特色。

yingyinNormal.en: Silicon Valley's a very provincial town. I can't get a job anywhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 硅谷是个小地方，出了这事我就找不到工作了。

yingyinNormal.en: The opera house that was gassed, he removed all provincial governors after that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 剧院毒气事件，那之后他换掉了所有省长。

yingyinNormal.en: Former vice president to President Garrett Walker. Nothing but a provincial and petty pen-stealer. But I need him. I need all five on my side if I'm gonna win this election.
yingyinNormal.zh: 加勒特·沃克总统的前副总统。就是个眼光狭隘的的偷笔毛贼。但我需要他。要想赢得这次选举，我需要他们五个都支持我。
